Aviation pioneer Burt Rutan designed the GlobalFlyer, aiming to break records with Steve Fossett at the helm.
The solo, non-stop flight around the world faces challenges like an uncooperative jet stream.
Fossett's journey will pass major cities and test his endurance in the lightweight aircraft.
The mission, funded by Virgin Atlantic, involves meticulous planning and monitoring of weather conditions.
With the support of Scaled Composites and Kansas State University students, Fossett's historic flight represents a significant milestone in aviation history.
The world watches as Fossett embarks on a daring adventure to achieve the impossible.
